   WHO'S NEWS: Richard Lambert was named editor of the
Financial Times. He will be succeeded as deputy editor of the
Pearson PLC paper by Ian Hargreaves, who is director of news
and current affairs at the British Broadcasting Corp. Sir
Geoffrey Owen is stepping down Dec. 31 after a decade as
editor. In April, he will become director of the
business-policy program at the London School of Economics'
Centre for Economic Performance.
